{"title": "Prowling About Panama", "description": "In 1903, Panama became a brand new state in Central America by seceding from Colombia in order to facilitate the construction of the Panama Canal, which was finished in 1914. This fledgling nation was home to the oldest inhabited European settlement on the American continent, a rich indigenous culture, and a splendid natural beauty from coast to jungle. <br><br>\r\n\r\nSuch was the scene as found by George A. Miller as he was \"Prowling about Panama\" in 1919, an activity that is more a \"getting lost in the right way\" than systematic exploration. Follow the author on his prowls through an amazing country that at the time of writing was an exciting mixture of tradition and modernity. (Summary by Ava). ", "duration": 19081, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "12538", "name": "George A. Miller"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/prowling_about_panama_2106_librivox/prowlingpanama_2106.jpg", "copyright_year": "1919", "genres": ["Travel & Geography", "Modern (20th C)"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Availle"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Availle"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "DaveC"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Foreword", "readers": [11064], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/prowling_about_panama_2106_librivox/prowlingaboutpanama_00_miller_64kb.mp3", "duration": 191}, {"section": 1, "title": "Where the Prowling is Good", "readers": [11064], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/prowling_about_panama_2106_librivox/prowlingaboutpanama_01_miller_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1022}, {"section": 2, "title": "The Trail of the Pirates", "readers": [15818], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/prowling_about_panama_2106_librivox/prowlingaboutpanama_02_miller_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1141}, {"section": 3, "title": "Picturesque Panama", "readers": [10244], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/prow